{
  "name": "PPO clip: why the trust region stops a runaway update",
  "description": "Two states, three actions. The new policy prefers action 0 in state 0 more strongly than the old policy did, so its probability ratio exceeds 1+epsilon. Turn on Verbose mode to watch ratio = exp(logp_new - logp_old), the clamp to [1-eps, 1+eps], and the min(ratio*A, clipped*A) that defines the surrogate — for the positive-advantage sample the clipped branch wins, removing the incentive to push the policy any further.",
  "nodes": [
